        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: UX-013 — design system documentation",
        "body": "Adds `ui/docs/design-system/` with 5 files documenting the glass surface system, color tokens with WCAG contrast ratios, motion standards, and an accessibility checklist.\n\n## Files added\n\n- `README.md` — index + one-paragraph summary of the design language and five guiding principles\n- `glass-surfaces.md` — two glass tiers with exact CSS values as-found in source, no-solid-panels rule, `@supports` fallback pattern, anti-patterns\n- `color-tokens.md` — full token table with dark/light values, intended use, contrast ratios on dark bg, anti-patterns\n- `motion.md` — duration scale (`--duration-fast/normal/slow`), easing tokens, `prefers-reduced-motion` pattern, animation inventory sourced from actual codebase\n- `accessibility.md` — WCAG 2.1 AA checklist: contrast minimums, `:focus-visible` pattern, 44px tap targets, skip link, focus trap, ARIA labels, `role=\"tab\"` pattern, reduced-motion, testing tools\n\nAll values reflect reality (read directly from `base.css`, `chat/layout.css`, `components.css`), not assumptions.\n\nPrevents design regressions and onboards contributors to the visual language.\n\nPart of UI/UX Enhancement Sprint 2.",
